      <data key="d9">["chapter:07"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0032">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">XOD format incompatible with byte-range requests</data>
      <data key="d29">The XOD format used by the Apprise viewer is not compatible with byte-range requests; it only renders the pages currently being viewed, so the whole PDF must be loaded into browser memory to manipulate visible pages.</data>
      <data key="d30">person:deon-kuhn</data>
      <data key="d31">[]</data>
      <data key="d7">0.9</data>
      <data key="d32">fact</data>
      <data key="d33">False</data>
      <data key="d28">1509.0</data>
      <data key="d8">[{"quote": "Deon: So, with the date range filter, since you're in the appraise world, in that viewer, it's not compatible with the format that we use with the XOD because that uses byte range requests, and it only renders the pages that you're viewing, basically.", "ts": 1509.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Deon: So, we rely heavily for that solution that the entire PDF has been loaded into the memory of the browser so that it can manipulate the pages that are visible.", "ts": 1509.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d9">["chapter:08"]</data>
    </node>
