    <node id="decision:0003">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Implement redaction inside DocSorter at the sorting stage</data>
      <data key="d29">Redaction should be implemented inside DocSorter at the sorting stage, since clinicians are the people best placed to perform the actual redaction, rather than as a single solution covering everything.</data>
      <data key="d35">["person:deon-kuhn"]</data>
      <data key="d36">Clinicians would be the people who are best placed to do the actual redaction in the first place.</data>
      <data key="d37">tentative</data>
      <data key="d28">1387.0</data>
      <data key="d38">["A single unified solution attempting to solve everything at once (Chantal's original ticket approach), which was found not to work and needed to be broken up into separate solutions (redaction in DocSorter, annotations attached to a page, etc.)."]</data>
      <data key="d7">0.9</data>
      <data key="d8">[{"quote": "Deon: So, redaction, my thinking, I might have mentioned this, is also that we do redaction inside DocSorter because they're the people who, the clinicians would be the people who are best placed to do the actual redaction in the first place.", "ts": 1387.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Deon: And that's why I feel like Chantal's original ticket was trying to find something that will solve everything, but it actually can't. But you do need to break it up into separate solutions. And redaction in DocSorter is, like, one part of that.", "ts": 1387.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d9">["chapter:07"]</data>
    </node>
