      <data key="d55">Rowan.Reid@MB-CPT-LT-0021 annotations % ./mri133 gen-corpus
generated 12 documents, 108 pages into data/corpus
Rowan.Reid@MB-CPT-LT-0021 annotations % ./mri133 resort
re-sorted 1 document(s) -&gt; data/resorted/  (originals in data/corpus/)

  removed_wrong_patient  9 -&gt; 8  a wrong-patient page is deleted (must be flagged removed, not slid to a neighbour)
  removed_benign         9 -&gt; 8  an ordinary page is removed
  split                  9 -&gt; 10  one page is split into two children (annotation duplicates; redaction abstains)
  clone                  9 -&gt; 11  one page is placed in several locations
  full_repagination       9 -&gt; 9  every page index changes at once
  inserted_indent        9 -&gt; 10  pages inserted with indent numbering between existing pages
  reorder                9 -&gt; 9  pages reordered without removal (a re-sort)
  composed_resort        9 -&gt; 10  a realistic re-sort: remove wrong-patient, split a page, clone a page, repaginate

Open a re-sorted PDF next to its original to see the change, e.g.:
  open data/corpus/matter-000-doc-00.clean.pdf data/resorted/matter-000-doc-00.composed_resort.pdf
Rowan.Reid@MB-CPT-LT-0021 annotations %</data>
