    <node id="visual:0009">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Screen share: MRI-133 bake-off results (content arm vs stamped arm)</data>
      <data key="d7">0.9</data>
      <data key="d8">[{"quote": "open data/corpus/matter-000-doc-00.clean.pdf data/resorted/matter-000-doc-00.composed_resort.pdf\nRowan.Reid@MB-CPT-LT-0021 annotations % ./mri133 run --matchers all\n=====================================================================\nMRI-133 matching bake-off -- these two arms answer DIFFERENT questions\nreference type: ANNOTATION | 12 docs x 8 §9 scenarios\n=====================================================================\n\nCONTENT ARM -- the AS-IS answer for the page-less population (nothing stamped):\n  precision/recall reported separately; silent-error and review-queue as a PAIR\n  exact_hash      P 92.9% R 89.7% abst-ok 81.2% silent 5.6% / queue 22.2%\n    worst: SPLIT 100% silent, REMOVED 33% silent, DUPLICATE 7% silent\n  perceptual      P 30.8% R 6.9% abst-ok 23.7% silent 12.5% / queue 81.9%\n    worst: INSERTED_INDENT 100% silent, REMOVED 33% silent\n  text_fingerprint P 60.0% R 25.9% abst-ok 27.7% silent 13.9% / queue 65.3%\n    worst: BLANK 100% silent, SPLIT 100% silent, REMOVED 33% silent\n  ensemble        P 70.7% R 60.9% abst-ok 59.1% silent 20.4% / queue 30.6%\n    worst: INSERTED_INDENT 100% silent, SPLIT 100% silent, REMOVED 33% silent\n  DoD reading (content-arm ensemble): POOR  [bars PROPOSED (pending decision): precision&gt;=0.95, recall&gt;=0.7, queue&lt;=0.3]\n\nSTAMPED ARM -- an 'if we stamp at extraction' PROJECTION (not today's population):\n  stamped_id      P 77.8% R 96.6% abst-ok N/A silent 22.2% / queue 0.0%\n    worst: DUPLICATE 100% silent, SPLIT 100% silent\n\n(run with --by-case for the full per-scenario table)\n\nSYNTHETIC-vs-REAL delta: real pairs N/A (synthetic only).\n  ** synthetic is a LOWER BOUND on difficulty; the real-pair delta is deferred Milestone C **\n=====================================================================\n\n(machine-readable result written to data/bakeoff.json)\n(visual report with every percentage's complement written to data/bakeoff.html)\nRowan.Reid@MB-CPT-LT-0021 annotations %", "ts": 946.5, "source": "vision"}]</data>
