    <node id="visual:0010">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Screen share: bakeoff.html visual results (content arm, exact_hash and perceptual)</data>
      <data key="d7">0.9</data>
      <data key="d8">[{"quote": "master split (of all pages) exactly one bucket; these add up to 100%\n72.2%   Correct 72.2% (624/864)  Silent error (confident &amp; WRONG) 5.6% (48/864)  Over-abstain (needless queue) 18.1% (156/864)\nRecall 89.7% of actionable pages: of pages where a confident answer was wanted, how many did it get right?\n89.7%   Found (correct) 89.7% (624/696)  Missed (wrong or needlessly queued) 10.3% (72/696)\nAbstention judgement 81.2% of all pages: of the pages it hands to a human vs handles itself\n77.8%  Sent to queue 22.2% (192/864)  Right to abstain 81.2% (156/192)  Needless (over-abstain) 18.8% (36/192)\n\npages whose content did not change and simply moved: ordinary, reordered, and inserted pages, and even form letters (their fingerprints differ).\nsplitting: a cut page's halves are physically new content, so it wrongly declares the page gone. It also cannot confirm a clone, so it safely queues it.\ncontent is untouched, blind the moment content is physically altered.\n\nCONTENT ARM   n = 864 page-outcomes\nprint of what the page looks like, not its exact bytes. A small visual change (scanner noise, a slight skew) barely moves the fingerprint, how visually alike two pages are.\n\nmaster split (of all pages)\n62.5%  Correct 5.6% (48/864)  Silent error (confident &amp; WRONG) 12.5% (108/864)  Over-abstain (needless queue) 62.5% (540/864)  correct to queue 19.4% (168/864)\nRecall 6.9% of actionable pages: of pages where a confident answer was wanted, how many did it get right?\n6.9%   Found (correct) 6.9% (48/696) ... 93.1%", "ts": 1098.75, "source": "vision"}]</data>
