Recall 6.9% of actionable pages: of pages where a confident answer was wanted, how many did it get right?
6.9%   Found (correct) 6.9% (48/696) ... 93.1%</data>
      <data key="d39">Browser-rendered HTML report (bakeoff.html) with bar charts breaking down precision, recall, and abstention judgement for the exact_hash and perceptual matchers within the content arm, plus explanatory notes on why perceptual hashing fails on split pages (content is physically altered) and succeeds on moved/reordered pages (fingerprint unchanged).</data>
